        <bioghist id="ref4">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Harry Gannes (1901-1941), at one time served (during the Popular Front era, c1935-c1939) as the foreign editor of the 
                <emph render="italic">Daily Worker</emph>, the newspaper of the Communist Party, USA.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The collection consists of "From the Cradle to the Factory," an undated (c1930s), unpublished typescript, 43 pp., about child labor in the United States. Table of contents: Child laborers we have always with us--How many are there?--Child labor on the job--The joy of the children in the wide open spaces--What child labor means to the working class--What shall be done?--Where child labor Is abolished.</p>
            <p>PLEASE DIRECT FURTHER INQUIRIES TO: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
